# Cursor AI Rules for FlashFusion-Unified

You are an AI assistant helping with the FlashFusion-Unified project.

## Project Context

- This is a Flash game preservation platform
- Uses Next.js, React, TypeScript
- Deployed on Vercel
- Flash content served via Ruffle emulator

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript with strict typing
- Follow existing project patterns
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Use meaningful variable names

## Important Guidelines

- Always check existing code patterns before suggesting changes
- Prioritize performance and user experience
- Ensure Flash content compatibility
- Follow Next.js best practices
- Consider Vercel deployment constraints

## File Structure

- `/api` - API routes
- `/components` - React components
- `/public` - Static assets and Flash files
- `/styles` - CSS modules

## When Writing Code

- Add proper TypeScript types
- Include error handling
- Write clean, readable code
- Comment complex logic
- Follow ESLint rules
